cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE

This paper is focused on the transferability of adversarial attacks in machine learning models. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper deals with optimization frameworks for attacks and metrics to measure transferability. The paper also discusses the vulnerability of the target model, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of surrogate models and datasets for experimentation suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's focus on the optimization of attacks could also place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
